tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=26}] ["",{color:"yellow",text:"Version 1.1.2 - "},{color:"#4BEDED",text:"A Kick in the Arsenal - Part 3"},{color:"gray",text:" | "},{color:"yellow",text:"Build Date: 1/24/26"},"\n",{color:"#ffcc25",text:"",extra:[{bold:true,text:"  • "},\
{\
    underlined:true,text:"Major Changes",hover_event:{\
        action:"show_text",value:["",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Added Tinctures of Healthiness, Toughness, and Potency. Each type has multiple tiers and has both Runic Table recipes and Crafting Table recipes."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Added Spell Scripts and the Scriptscrying Table. Spell Scripts are the new default way to unlock spells, being found throughout the world or from achieving certain milestones. By placing them in a Scriptscrying Table, a user may play out a minigame that, upon successful completion, rewards the user with the inscribed spell's knowledge."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Spell Scripts have been added to all Necrosculker loot tables. Also, they can be dropped by vanilla bosses, with each enemy offering a different pool of potential spell scripts."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Introduced Spellcrafting system. Now, equipped gear and enchantments can alter how your spells behave in many ways."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Added Attunement enchantments for Tablets. These enchantments come in the form of various elements, and improve spells that fall under their respective element in various ways, depending on the element and spell. There are Greater and Lesser Attunement enchantments, and only one of each may be applied at a time."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Reworked Echo internally such that any level can have a respective speed and damage amount. This means that Echo can go above level 3 and won't require hardcoded values to function properly (only up to level 3 is obtainable for now)."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • With this rework to Echo, it has also been heavily nerfed to only allow 3 Echo Clouds to be summoned at any given time, per player."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Reworked the natural method of increasing Max Health. Now, instead of being purely based on eating unique food types, players will gain additional HP for completing Advancements. Every vanilla Advancement is implemented, and all of the Advancements under the Runic Resurgence family of datapacks will be compatible as well."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Modified the Necrosculker fights further. Across most tiers, Elite excluded, the Necrosculker's health has been reduced. This is more substantial with the higher tiers. Additionally, Tier 3 and 4 Necrosculkers will only fire 4 lasers during the second Laser Phase, but they move faster and deal even more true damage. The base damage of most other attacks has been increased across the board as well."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • With the increased base health granted by the altered Health system, damage received by players has been increased across the board by 10%. This is to give a more satisfying boost to the feel of progression while also keeping a level of balance."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Added the Extension enchantment, which is exclusive to chestplates. Each of its 4 levels increases Entity and Block Reach by 0.5 blocks."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Added the Aegis enchantment, which is exclusive to shields. Each of its 3 levels allows a shield to repair itself by 1% of total durability per level, per point of damage blocked."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Fixed a massive bug with Echo that prevented it from damaging the Necrosculker."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Re-implemented the Magic Bolt (now Arcane Bolt) spell. Arcane Bolt now has a unique ability to be modified extraordinarily heavily by the Spellcrafting system. Many stats and modifiers can now be placed on the spell to change almost every aspect of its function."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Re-implemented the Enchanted Shield (now Paladin's Pylon) spell. Paladin's Pylon is no longer a temporary Resistance buff, and is instead replaced with a stationary shield which absorbs all damage from players within its radius. The shield itself has a limited health pool and dispells after its health is expended or after a short timer."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Players now have a very limited spell pool to start with, those being Arcane Bolt and Paladin's Pylon. Every other spell in the pack must be found and deciphered through Spell Scripts."},"\n",\
    ]}\
}," (hover to see)"]},"\n",{color:"blue",text:"",extra:[{bold:true,text:"  • "},\
{\
    underlined:true,text:"Minor Changes",hover_event:{action:"show_text",value:["",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Fixed a bug where one of the Necrosculker's attacks wouldn't properly cause damage."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Fixed a couple minor spelling mistakes and incorrect information from Part 2."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Rebalanced a bit of the Necrosculker's Summons. Now, Berserkers/Shredders have a higher chance of spawning over the other two types. Also, Paladin types have been nerfed slightly so they are less frustrating."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Fixed a large bug which caused the Recovery enchantment to be far too potent."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Improvements to Havenite Meteors. When falling, they are no longer blocked from falling North. Also, Tenebrium Pickaxes grant a higher mining speed than Netherite for these meteors."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Removed the datapack \"watermarks\" for enchantments on items and books."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Fixed a bug where the Elite Necrosculker would sometimes leave behind attack markers, which would unintentionally make subsequent fights in the same arena harder."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Added an Enchantment Order tag to push enchantments for Runic Resurgence in order below all vanilla enchantments."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Fixed a bug which allowed the Weakness debuff to massively delay health regeneration when hit repeatedly. While it is already supposed to delay regeneration, it could cause minutes or hours of delay under the right (or wrong?) circumstances."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Fixed some numbers with all Necrosculker tiers, namely how they calculate summoned skeleton counts for reabsorption and total max health including regeneration methods. No longer will the Void Necrosculker be able to regenerate to 15k health, instead it is 4k. Hooray!"},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Fixed several backend issues where the order of functions could break certain mechanics, namely with enchantments."},"\n",\
    ]}\
    }," (hover to see)"]}\
]
tellraw @s[advancements={aea_adv:enchantments/found_blessing_book=true},scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=26}] ["",{color:"#e839ff",text:"",extra:[{bold:true,text:"  • "},\
{\
    underlined:true,text:"Blessings and Vices:",hover_event:{\
        action:"show_text",value:["",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Added Titanism, Reverberation, Wanderlust, and Bastion Blessings."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Added Windbroken, Enraging, Exhaustion, and Distraction Vices."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Blessings and Vices will now always appear at the bottom of an item's enchantment list, with Blessings coming first."},"\n",\
    ]}\
}," (hover to see)"]}]
scoreboard players set @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=26}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 27

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=25}] ["",{color:"yellow",text:"Version 1.1.1 - "},{color:"#4BEDED",text:"A Kick in the Arsenal - Part 2"},{color:"gray",text:" | "},{color:"yellow",text:"Build Date: 7/27/25"},"\n",{color:"#FF8B39",text:"",extra:[{bold:true,text:"  • "},\
{\
    underlined:true,text:"Necrosculker Changes",hover_event:{\
        action:"show_text",value:["",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Variation: Improved the Necrosculker fight overall to be more varied at all tiers. Now, each set of summoned Crypt Keepers have a chance to be classified as Berserkers (axes, act as glass cannons), Warriors (swords, act as tanks), or Archers (bows, of course). Enchantments on items are improved or added with higher tiers. Additionally, Large Root Pods (the things you damage) spawn in random positions."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Buff: The Necrosculker has grown smarter! It will no longer cause damage to its summoned Skeletons when summoning Sculk Tendrils."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Buff: An additional attack has been added to the Nightmare and Void Necrosculker (Tiers 3 and 4). The boss will create an aura of Darkness damage around the arena that remains in one spot for an extended period of time."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Rework: The Necrosculker's second Laser phase (The Wall) has been removed from Tiers 1 and 2, and Tiers 2 and above now have a Tendril Wave phase (after recovering from Weakened phase). This phase consists of rows and circles of Sculk Tendrils appearing throughout the arena, some of which must be jumped over to avoid damage."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Loot Table Improvements: Each Necrosculker tier can now drop Dark Hearts for the tier below it as loot. These drop at a 66% rate per kill. Additionally, a big bug with the Sculk Critter Companion has been resolved, and they should now actually drop."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • New Mechanic: Each Necrosculker tier now has consistent weakpoints that may be attacked throughout the fight. These weakpoints take 1/8 of normal damage and have a limited health pool. Once depleted, they cause a rush of Tendrils to appear throughout the arena, damage the boss a large amount, and then retreat into the ground to regenerate."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • QOL: Some of the Necrosculker's attacks have been given improvements for visibility purposes, especially the laser attacks."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • QOL: The Necrosculker will now drop a Loot Bag to every player that took part in the fight. Loot Bags can be opened by right-clicking them while holding them, and drop the same loot as the Necrosculker did before."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Massive backend improvements. There should (hopefully) be significantly less lag when fighting all tiers."},\
    ]}\
}," (hover to see)"]},"\n",{color:"#ffcc25",text:"",extra:[{bold:true,text:"  • "},\
{\
    underlined:true,text:"Other Major Changes",hover_event:{\
        action:"show_text",value:["",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • The Arcana Altar is now a craftable/placeable block instead of a stationary multiblock structure. Its recipe and details can now be viewed in the Runic Compendium."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Introduced Tenebrium Tools, Sword, Shield, and Crossbow. These items are craftable using the Runic Manipulation Table and have been added to the Runic Compendium. Tenebrium Tools and Swords have additional block/entity reach, depending on which item is used."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • The Arcana Altar's xp level prices have been reduced by roughly 33%. This is in preparation for an additional item cost that will come later."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Improved Death Protection detection when dying using Lifeline (the data pack). Now, Totems will be cleared first, and other items with Death Protection will no longer be deleted entirely."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Increased the base HP Regeneration rate to 1% of Max HP per second instead of 0.5%. (This does not affect other things like the Regeneration effect or Tinctures)."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Added Crafting Table versions of Healing Tincture recipes for convenience and mass-crafting."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Added Tomahawks for all materials, which can be thrown."},"\n",\
    ]}\
}," (hover to see)"]},"\n",{color:"blue",text:"",extra:[{bold:true,text:"  • "},{underlined:true,text:"Minor Changes",hover_event:{action:"show_text",value:["",\
    {\
        color:"gold",text:"  • Fixed a couple minor spelling mistakes and incorrect information from Part 1."}]}\
    }," (hover to see)"]}\
]
tellraw @s[advancements={aea_adv:enchantments/found_blessing_book=true},scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=25}] ["",{color:"#e839ff",text:"",extra:[{bold:true,text:"  • "},\
{\
    underlined:true,text:"Blessings and Vices:",hover_event:{\
        action:"show_text",value:["",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Buffed Pressure Blessing to deal more damage to other targets and less damage to the user."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Buffed Foresight Blessing to heal the user a small amount when performing a Perfect Block."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Added Boomstick Blessing for Crossbows."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Added Downpour Blessing for Bows and Crossbows."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Added Straining Vice for Bows."},"\n",\
    ]}\
}," (hover to see)"]}]
scoreboard players set @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=25}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 26

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=24}] ["",{color:"yellow",text:"Version 1.1 - "},{color:"#4BEDED",text:"A Kick in the Arsenal - Part 1"},{color:"gray",text:" | "},{color:"yellow",text:"Build Date: 7/9/25"},"\n",{color:"#FF8B39",text:"",extra:[{bold:true,text:"  • "},\
{\
    underlined:true,text:"Major Changes",hover_event:{\
        action:"show_text",value:["",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Added Transmission Nexuses and Transmission Pylons, which act as lightweight Waystones. Also added Ender Dust to be used as payment for teleportation."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Sculk and Tenebrium Bows now actually apply additional arrow speed."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Added the Slipstream enchantment for Happy Ghast Harnesses. This enchantment improves the speed of a Happy Ghast depending on how high it flies. Each level expands on both the max speed and height required to obtain it."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Shrink and Enlarge have had their speed modifications swapped. Now, Enlarge makes you slower, and Shrink makes you faster."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Consuming \"bad\" food (such as Rotten Flesh, Pufferfish, Poisonous Potato, etc.) no longer grants 5 Max HP. This health is given to players outright to lessen the brutality of the early-game. All players should now start out with 100 Max HP at minimum. Overall Max HP gained from food is now 400."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Added the Bolster Enchantment for Chestplates. Bolster increases your Max HP by +20 per level, up to +100 at level 5."},"\n",\
        {color:"gold",text:"  • Added the Recovery Enchantment for Chestplates. Recovery increases your Regeneration Rate by +0.8% of Max HP per second per level, up to +4% per second at level 5."},"\n",\
        {color:"blue",text:"  • Added Tinctures, which act as special effect or lightweight potions. They are craftable significantly earlier on than normal potions and stack to 16."}\
    ]}\
}," (hover to see)"]},"\n",{color:"blue",text:"",extra:[{bold:true,text:"  • "},{underlined:true,text:"Minor Changes",hover_event:{action:"show_text",value:["",\
    {\
        color:"gold",text:"  • Nothing here!"}]}\
    }," (hover to see)"]}\
]
scoreboard players set @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=24}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 25

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=23}] ["",{color:"yellow",text:"Version 1.0.2 - "},{color:"#4BEDED",text:"Meteoric Melodies"},{color:"gray",text:" | "},{color:"yellow",text:"Build Date: 7/1/25"},"\n",{color:"#FF8B39",text:"",extra:[{bold:true,text:"  • "},{underlined:true,text:"Major Changes",hover_event:{action:"show_text",value:["",{color:"blue",text:"  • Havenite Meteorites can now be instantly cleared through the use of the Meteoric Enchantment. This Enchantment is specific to pickaxes and will repair the pickaxe when clearing a meteorite."},"\n",{color:"gold",text:"  • A simple recipe has been added for the Runic Compendium."},"\n",{color:"blue",text:"  • Knowledge Fragments are now usable and grant a peek into the lore of the world. Using \"/trigger rr.trigger.show_knowledge\" will allow you to select from all obtained knowledge."},"\n",{color:"gold",text:"  • Updated the Havenite Meteorite page in the Runic Compendium with the recently-changed loot table and removal method."},"\n",{color:"blue",text:"  • Added Music Discs for Lost in Loss, Sinking Feeling, and all Deep Trouble variants. Recipes are listed in the Runic Compendium, under the Other Items category."},"\n",{color:"gold",text:"  • Added advancements for a couple things like finding a Lonely Home and mining a Havenite Meteorite."},"\n",{color:"blue",text:"  • Fixed where Lonely Home chests would used incorrect Loot Table namespaces."},"\n",{color:"gold",text:"  • Gave a very small damage nerf to Echo enchantment. New stats are listed in the Runic Compendium."},"\n",{color:"blue",text:"  • Moderately reduced the frequency of Ancient Crypts, as they were pretty overtuned."}]}}," (hover to see)"]},"\n",{color:"blue",text:"",extra:[{bold:true,text:"  • "},{underlined:true,text:"Minor Changes",hover_event:{action:"show_text",value:["",{color:"gold",text:"  • Mildly reduced the sound of completing a craft at the Runic Manipulation Table."}]}}," (hover to see)"]}]
scoreboard players set @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=23}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 24

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=22}] ["",{color:"yellow",text:"Version 1.0.1 - "},{color:"#4BEDED",text:"That Thing Is Too Loud!"},{color:"gray",text:" | "},{color:"yellow",text:"MC Version 1.21.6"},"\n",{color:"#FF8B39",text:"",extra:[{bold:true,text:"  • "},{underlined:true,text:"Major Changes",hover_event:{action:"show_text",value:["",{color:"blue",text:"  • Havenite Meteors are now a 1/8 chance per day instead of 1/5. Their spawn sounds are significantly reduced and much more pleasing to the ears. Havenite Meteor Chunks have been added as a rare drop from Meteors by default (no Silk Touch required)."},"\n",{color:"gold",text:"  • Runic Manipulation Tables can no longer overwrite non-full blocks on placement."},"\n",{color:"blue",text:"  • Lifeline's Heal sound is now off by default, but can be enabled by using \"/trigger sbhp.trigger.ToggleHealSound\". It is also slightly quieter."},"\n",{color:"gold",text:"  • Fixed a bug where some players riding on mounts would not be able to see their mount's Health or Armor values."}]}}," (hover to see)"]},"\n",{color:"blue",text:"",extra:[{bold:true,text:"  • "},{underlined:true,text:"Minor Changes",hover_event:{action:"show_text",value:["","\n",{color:"gold",text:"  • Uh, nothing."},"\n"]}}," (hover to see)"]}]
scoreboard players set @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=22}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 23

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=21}] ["",{color:"yellow",text:"Version 1.0 - "},{color:"#4BEDED",text:"Tales from the Reliquary"},{color:"gray",text:" | "},{color:"yellow",text:"MC Version 1.21.6"},"\n",{color:"#FF8B39",text:"",extra:[{bold:true,text:"  • "},{underlined:true,text:"Major Changes",hover_event:{action:"show_text",value:["",{color:"blue",text:"  • The Runic Manipulation Table has been given some nice QOL. When clicking a filled slot with the same item, the slot will be cleared without placing that same item back in."},"\n",{color:"gold",text:"  • The Necrosculker has been reintroduced. The boss has new music and improved loot tables. Future updates will modify its attack patterns, but there is little to no change in the fight itself at the moment. It also has had major backend improvements to cut down on lag and bugs."},"\n",{color:"blue",text:"  • Echo, Fervor, Recursion, Rebound, Tether, Gift of Gravity, and a couple new additions are now actual enchantments. Some of these have been added to the Enchanting Table, but they will primarily be obtained through the Arcana Altar."},"\n",{color:"gold",text:"  • A new material has been introduced to supercede Netherite. Tenebrium Ingots must be crafted through the use of various Necrosculker drops, and only armor, a Falchion, and a Bow is available currently."},"\n",{color:"blue",text:"  • The Runic Manipulation Table now displays a preview of the item being crafted before using up the materials, in case the user doesn't actually want to craft the item. To finalize the craft, the user must click the preview item."},"\n",{color:"gold",text:"  • Many, many improvements to code, granting a noticeable improvement to performance and smooshing several nasty bugs."},"\n",{color:"blue",text:"  • Rebound has received an overhaul. Arrows launched by a Rebound bow will now bounce off of walls, floors and ceilings and continue their trajectory properly, as if actually hitting a surface and bouncing off of it."},"\n",{color:"gold",text:"  • Recursion has received an overhaul as well. Arrows launched by a Recursion bow will no longer explode in a payload of arrows upon landing, but instead will cause a repeated, delayed duplicate of the arrow to be sent out from the same location and with the same data (enchantments, critical status, damage, velocity). The enchantment now only goes up to level 3, whereby one arrow causes three duplicate arrows to be sent out."},"\n",{color:"blue",text:"  • Multishot and Piercing have been added as part of the list of enchantments that may be applied to Bows and Crossbows through the Arcana Altar."},"\n",{color:"gold",text:"  • Recursion and Rebound are now only semi-mutually-exclusive. If a bow has two of the three enchantments of Multishot, Recursion, or Rebound, then the third enchantment becomes mutually exclusive with the other two. However, any two of these enchantments may be applied together now."},"\n",{color:"blue",text:"  • Echo has received an overhaul. Instead of creating a damaging cloud on hit with a cooldown, it instead has a small chance (increasing with each level) to create a forward-moving version of the cloud without a cooldown."},"\n",{color:"gold",text:"  • Fervor has been slightly nerfed so that keeping the maximum strength is slightly harder and doesn't last as long without attacking. Also, holding an item without Fervor drastically increases the rate at which the Fervor Charge deteriorates."},"\n",{color:"blue",text:"  • Runic Resurgence will now utilize the re-made Health system designed in the Lifeline datapack (now a part of RR). Future bosses and spells will be intertwined with this feature and its mechanics heavily."},"\n",{color:"gold",text:"  • Temporarily added a way to obtain Sculk Essence without having to go to the Ancient Crypt (as the strucutre is still underway). Being in the Deep Dark will sometimes transform Skeletons and Zombies nearby into Infested and Infected, which will occasionally drop the item, as well as Deep Dark Knowledge Fragments."}]}}," (hover to see)"]},"\n",{color:"blue",text:"",extra:[{bold:true,text:"  • "},{underlined:true,text:"Minor Changes",hover_event:{action:"show_text",value:["",{color:"blue",text:"  • Added a new Darkness damage type, now used by the Necrosculker boss for some attacks. This damage type pierces through armor and all enchantments, but is affected by Resistance."},"\n",{color:"gold",text:"  • Fixed a particularly annoying bug where reloading the world and its data packs would sometimes cause a Havenite Meteor to fall."},"\n",{color:"blue",text:"  • Added several new paintings."},"\n",{color:"gold",text:"  • Added some breaking/placing sounds to Runic Manipulation Tables."},"\n",{color:"blue",text:"  • Improved and fleshed out several new and old pages in the Runic Compendium. The Items list is now subdivided into Materials, Equipment, Boss Items and Other categories."},"\n",{color:"gold",text:"  • Modified some item textures and animations."},"\n",{color:"blue",text:"  • Renamed some items to fit their new recipes."},"\n",{color:"gold",text:"  • Recursion and Rebound now work for enchantment levels above their built-in maximum. (They work up to level 255!)"},"\n",{color:"blue",text:"  • Hostile monsters can now spawn in with equipment enchanted with some Arcana Altar enchantments."},"\n",{color:"gold",text:"  • Updated and added new textures to each level of the Arcana Altar's new enchantments. Also temporarily added another resource pack's enchanted book textures for all vanilla enchantments. The resource pack is xali's Enchanted Books, by xalixilax. Link to Curseforge page in \"trigger rr.trigger.credits\"."}]}}," (hover to see)"]}]
scoreboard players set @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=21}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 22

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=20}] ["",{"text":"Version 0.17 - ","bold":true,"color":"light_purple"},{"text":"The Runic Revitalization","color":"light_purple","font":"rr_recast:alagard"},"\n",{"text":"  • ","bold":true,"color":"gold"},{"text":"Major Changes","bold":true,"underlined":true,"color":"gold","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"  • The Arcane Enchanting Altar and its future changes and additions have all been moved to a separate data pack, which will be optional (but still recommended) for RR 1.0 and beyond. This separate data pack also no longer requires RR to be installed to function. This is to heavily reduce the load both packs require on computers and servers, and to allow for easier updates. (NOTE: All items enchanted with the Arcane Enchanting Altar before this point will need to be updated!)\n","color":"blue"},{"text":"  • Reconstructed Spellcasting from the ground up. Spells now have specific stats associated with them, which can be changed through the use of equipment and enchantments. Alteration of spell stats is now called \"Spellcrafting\".\n","color":"gold"},{"text":"  • Introduced a new Random Event, the Havenite Meteor! This event allows players to obtain Havenite Shards if they dare to mine the precious meteorite that falls from the sky. These Shards can be used to craft Runic Tablets and their upgrades, apply special enchantments to gear, and unlock new and unique spells.\n","color":"blue"},{"text":"  • Due to this version necessitating a near-complete rewrite, many features have been disabled or removed temporarily. Such features include the Necrosculker boss battle, Companions, and several spells. These features will be re-introduced at a later date with many notable improvements to both performance and function.\n","color":"gold"},{"text":"  • Introduced the Runic Crafting Table, which enables an entire new family of crafting recipes. This table must be crafted in a Crafting Table, and must be powered with Havenite Meteor Chunks to function.\n","color":"blue"},{"text":"  • Added the Runic Compendium, an in-game wiki item that shows many details on everything in the pack. Can be crafted with 1 Book and 1 Paper in the Runic Crafting Table.\n","color":"gold"},{"text":"  • Added Tablet Variants. Each Tablet Tier now has 7 new and unique forms it can take, one of which is selected when crafted.\n","color":"blue"},{"text":"  • Re-implemented Catalystum Armor from a very old (and unreleased) data pack. Functionality not yet included. The base set can be crafted using Gilded Havenite Shards, Catalystum Ingots, and a Dormant Elemental Core.","color":"gold"}]}},"\n",{"text":"  • ","bold":true,"color":"gold"},{"text":"Minor Changes","bold":true,"underlined":true,"color":"blue","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"  • Runic Tablets have had further backend improvements. The Runic Ring has had a visual overhaul.\n","color":"blue"},{"text":"  • Introduced a new Font to be used in various places, credits in data pack files.\n","color":"gold"},{"text":"  • Re-created all items under the new Components system.","color":"blue"}]}}]
scoreboard players set @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=20}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 21


tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=19}] ["",{"text":"[Old] Version 0.16","underlined":true,"color":"blue","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Reworked the Runic Tablets and Musical Tablet. Runic Flames and Musical Flames can now be summoned omnidirectionally, and as a whole, they are significantly more efficient and way less laggy.","color":"aqua","italic":false},"\n",{"text":"Fixed the Deck of Cards recipe to correctly use 54 pieces of paper instead of 52 to account for Joker cards.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Altered how Necrosculker functions are carried out to be more efficient.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Added a way to make Netherite armor ","color":"green","italic":false},{"text":"unbreakable","color":"green","italic":true},{"text":". Craft the base armor with 1 Crest and 16 Obsidian (as well as with all prerequisite enchantments) to apply the Unbreakable modifier. Prerequisite enchantments are Unbreaking 5 and Mending. All other attributes of the armor will be preserved.","color":"green","italic":false},"\n",{"text":"Restored Golden Falchions will now properly lose their Enchantment glint when crafted.","color":"aqua","italic":false},"\n",{"text":"Added Vitality Essence as a possible drop for all Necrosculker variants.","color":"green","italic":false}]}}]
scoreboard players add @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=19}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 1

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=18}] ["",{"text":"[Old] Version 0.15","underlined":true,"color":"blue","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Introduced a Questing system into the game, with the first major quest being \"The Paladins' Catalyst,\" which can be started by finding a Desert Oasis structure in a Desert biome. (Do note that this quest will not have any actual features until later, it is just to have it present as a baseline and to have the structure generatable)","color":"aqua","italic":false},"\n",{"text":"Sequel fights to the Necrosculker have been added in the form of an Elite variant, a Nightmare variant, and a Void variant. The variants are significantly more difficult but also carry much more rewarding loot pools. These forms can be summoned with Dark Hearts, which are explained later.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Added the Baby Sculk Creature Companion, Deep Dark Crest, 3 new Knowledge Fragments, and a secret item as drops from Elite and higher Necrosculkers.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Added a way to create Vitality Essence from unwanted Companions. To create the essence, see the Runic Resurgence Guide advancements page.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Fleshed out some textures in the Resource Pack. Also added animations to some items.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Changed the way that Companions are displayed when equipped. They will now stay directly by their owners at all times. Their position can be changed around using a new compPosition trigger.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Summoning a Necrosculker boss now requires a unique Summon Item rather than raw materials so that it's easier to actually get the fight started. Recipes for individual summon items are in the Runic Resurgence Guide advancements page.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Temporarily modified Echo to not damage players. A large bug causes the enchantment to sometimes damage the player that spawns the Echo cloud, and with no easy fix available, it will have to wait.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Heavily nerfed Echo. Echo clouds can now only be spawned if using a sword to damage something. Spells and Bows (and, more notably, their enchantments) will no longer proc Echo even if a sword with Echo is held.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"The Necrosculker's Skeletons will now be affected by Slowness. As well, the Sculk Root Pods (the boss's weakpoints) will be able to be hit for full damage multiple times successively, allowing for multiple players to attack one pod at the same time without missing damage. Weakpoints that take damage will also spawn experience orbs to lessen the effect of damage on armor durability.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Added the Restored Golden Falchion and Soulsalve, with recipes in the Runic Resurgence Guide advancements page.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Added Jokers to the Deck of Cards, can be obtained through a give function or though crafting the whole deck.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Added several new advancements to the Runic Resurgence Goals page.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"All Armor types and enchantments are now compatible with the Arcane Enchanting Altar. There are no custom enchantments (yet), but vanilla enchantments may be raised above vanilla maximums.","color":"green","italic":false}]}}]
scoreboard players add @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=18}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 1

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=17}] ["",{"text":"[Old] Version 0.14","underlined":true,"color":"blue","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Fixed a few typos and corrected instructions dealing with the Arcane Enchanting Altar and some enchantment descriptions.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Cut down on lagginess by changing when and where certain things execute.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"A Deck of Cards has been added with a crafting recipe to get all of the cards at once. These will likely not have functionality aside from being the cards themselves. You can see this recipe in the Runic Resurgence Guide advancement page, in the Items category.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Fixed incorrect level displays for some enchantments when clicking the \"Max Level\" button. Also fixed reversed item displays for Minecraft 1.20 Snapshot 23w16a's Item Display changes.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"The Rebound enchantment is now significantly more reliable and effective. The arrows shot using this enchantment will no longer have to climb walls or get stuck on ceilings.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Sunstruck and Moonstruck will now apply to the Recursion enchantment's spawned arrows.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Modified the Loot Table for the Necrosculker. The Sculk Falchion is now a 1/80 drop rather than a 1/200 drop due to its general rarity from structures being annoying.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Added the Deep Dark Bow as a 1/80 drop from the Necrosculker. The bow comes with a built-in boost to arrow speed, and ","color":"green"},{"text":"cannot","color":"green","italic":true},{"text":" be obtained from Ancient Crypts.","color":"green","italic":false},"\n",{"text":"Added the Protractor Bow, which tells its user the exact distance between their position and where the arrow lands. A recipe may be seen in the Runic Resurgence Guide advancements page.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Nearly entirely revamped the \"Catastrophe Paladin\" song. It is still unfinished, but more closely aligns with the desired vibe.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Endermen can no longer pick up blocks by request (likely will move to another datapack in the future)","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Added a statistic for \"Altar Enchantments Performed\" and for \"Greatest Arrow Distance Using Protractor Bow\"","color":"green"}]}}]
scoreboard players add @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=17}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 1

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=16}] ["",{"text":"[Old] Version 0.13","underlined":true,"color":"blue","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Added the Echo and Fervor enchantments for Swords. Also added the Recursion, Sunstruck, Moonstruck, Gift of Gravity, Tether, and Rebound Enchantments for Bows. These are all available in the Arcane Enchanting Altar.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"The Arcane Enchanting Altar has a node in the Runic Resurgence Guide advancement page.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"A guide for creating and using the Arcane Enchanting Altar has been added. A text-based guide will appear as you use the table and can be turned off with \"/trigger toggleAltarGuide\". An additional guide for creating and removing the Altar can be seen by using \"/trigger showAltarDesc\"","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Altars are now fully compatible with all possible sword and bow enchantments, and each enchantment has a new maximum (aside from Mending and Infinity, because increasing the level of these adds nothing).","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Mending and Infinity are no longer mutually exclusive with each other. One of these enchantments will have to be applied with the Arcane Enchanting Altar if both are desired on one bow for an increased price.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Fixed the ongoing bug with Return breaking spellcasting when failing the cast.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Fixed an issue with Runic Resurgence's custom trim colors breaking. They will now display properly.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Fixed a bug that caused some enchanted books from the Ancient Crypt chest to be \"improperly enchanted,\" causing them to not function properly.","color":"green"}]}}]
scoreboard players add @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=16}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 1

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=15}] ["",{"text":"[Old] Version 0.12","underlined":true,"color":"blue","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Added the Alchemize Spell [24895 | T2].","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Buffed the Heal Type Dirt Companion. It now heals players every 5 seconds instead of every 6 seconds. Also, it will only attempt to heal players who are not at max health, so the sound and particle effect will not constantly play when it is not necessary.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Fixed an error with the Effect Type Dirt Companion item. It now correctly displays that it improves Speed by 20%, rather than 10%.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Added the Stone Companion, Zombie Companion, and Bat Companion.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Special drops (companions, Knowledge Fragments, Deep Dark Cores, etc.) now display a message and play a sound when they are dropped.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Implemented the base for the Arcane Enchanting Altar. For the time being, it only works as a decoration, but items may still be inserted and taken out freely.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Added the Onyx Gemstone as a drop from Bats. These will be useful for the next large features planned.","color":"aqua"}]}}]
scoreboard players add @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=15}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 1

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=14}] ["",{"text":"[Old] Version 0.11","underlined":true,"color":"blue","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Added XP Shuffle Spells: Feed [87591 | T4], Heal [87592 | T3], and Mend [87593 | T3]. Each of these use XP as a resource instead of items.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Buffed the Jukebox. It now plays Runic Resurgence music to players that are further away, up to 50 blocks.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Fixed more bugs with the Fools' Gold spell. Also made the range at which Cleanse removes items to be its full range of 8 blocks instead of 4.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Fixed several errors with spell execution where multiple players in the same vicinity could cause spells to trigger effects multiple times per player, which would create unpredictable and erratic behavior.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Added Cherries, just because why not?","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Added a new Companions system. This system allows players to find and equip small creatures which help their owner in a multitude of ways. Some Companions will need to be crafted, some can be found in chests, and some might be discovered as drops from blocks or enemies.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Added 4 Dirt Companions (Cosmetic, Damage, Heal, and Stat Types) which act as a sort of introduction to how the system may work and expand in the future.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Rebranded Runic Spells! It is now Runic Resurgence, as spells are no longer the only focus for this datapack. This also alludes to a bigger story that encapsulates everything that is planned.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Added Ancient Music Discs that play songs for Runic Resurgence that aren't implemented yet. They will be removed once their respective song is put into an actual feature.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Fixed an issue with the Lonely Home structure where one of the chests would always generate the same loot.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Added a statistic for Total Companion Damage Dealt.","color":"aqua"}]}}]
scoreboard players add @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=14}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 1

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=13}] ["",{"text":"[Old] Version 0.10.2","underlined":true,"color":"blue","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Added a new structure: The Lonely Home. It can be found in any Taiga biome and Taiga variant biomes.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Fixed several bugs with the Fools' Gold spell.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Fixed a bug with Tendril Wave so that the alternating wave of tendrils does not harm the user.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Added a new Knowledge Fragment for the Lonely Home structure.","color":"green"}]}}]
scoreboard players add @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=13}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 1

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=12}] ["",{"text":"[Old] Version 0.10.1","underlined":true,"color":"blue","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Modified the crafting of Music Discs from the data pack. The recipe is the same, but now it uses the same glowing item frame / amethyst block station that other recipes use.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Balance changes for Enchanted Shield II - This spell now grants Resistance 3 instead of Resistance 2 for the last 8 seconds it is active so it remains stronger than a beacon when used.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Changed the positions at which Ancient Crypts may spawn. They can now be located only from Y=-50 to Y=-40, inclusive. Increased the maximum number of Ancient Crypt Keepers that can spawn inside from 8 -> 10.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Balance changes for Tendril Wave - The spell is now slightly better at hitting things where the tendrils shoot up from. They now hit targets slightly higher and lower than before. Additionally, the alternating tendril rings come up at different distances so more area is covered overall.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Major bug fix for Return - When failing to cast the spell (moving during the cast), players will no longer get stalled on their energy refreshing and will be able to cast spells as normal.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"More general performance improvements have been made in the background.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Descriptions on Runic Tablets and Tablets of Memory have been fixed for some loot tables.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Moved Tendril Wave's node in the Runic Resurgence Guide so that it is now placed with other area-of-effect spells.","color":"green"}]}}]
scoreboard players add @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=12}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 1

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=11}] ["",{"text":"[Old] Version 0.10","underlined":true,"color":"blue","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Added a new spell which is the first Special Tier spell. It's obtainable from the Necrosculker and must be learned through special crafting. This recipe can be seen in the Runic Resurgence Guide advancements page as an offshoot of the Necrosculker node.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Many balance changes for the Necrosculker have been made, including making the Sculk Tendrils much more dangerous and modifying how the lasers function. Additionally, going above (5.25 blocks) or below (1 block) the arena's floor will cause you to be teleported in the opposite direction.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Added several unique stats which track spells cast, magic damage done of all types, and kills for custom entities and bosses. These can be seen with \"/trigger showStats\".","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Added the Sculk Falchion to the Necrosculker's loot table as an extraordinarily rare drop (1/200).","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Modified the Enhanced Tablet of Memory recipe to use Raw Gold Blocks instead of Gold Blocks","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Several spells have been tweaked and bugs have been squashed. Most notably, Chaos Strike can no longer hit the caster and Ricochet Bolt's kills now count as the caster's kills.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"The Sculk Falchion is no longer upgraded in the Smithing Table. Instead, the Nethersculk Falchion has a special crafting recipe similar to other recipes within the data pack. You can see this recipe in the Runic Resurgence Guide advancements page.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"A significant rework of how spells run interally has been made to cut down on lag significantly.","color":"green"}]}}]
scoreboard players add @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=11}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 1

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=10}] ["",{"text":"[Old] Version 0.9","underlined":true,"color":"blue","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Added the Ricochet Bolt Spell [54721] and the Frost Cluster Spell [31859].","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Introduced Tiered Spells, overhauling the entire Spell system. Each spell now has a Tier associated with it. You can now also upgrade your Runic Tablets and Tablets of Memory up to 3 times; the materials for each upgrade as well as each spell's Tier is noted in the Runic Resurgence Guide page in the Advancements menu.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Ancient Shards and the Deep Dark Core now have uses for crafting Runic Tablet upgrades.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"All new Trims in the 1.20 Snapshot 23w12a have been added to the data pack. They now work for the advancements and with the custom trim colors. Loot tables have been altered so that they will contain new templates and data pack items.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"A new advancement has been added for obtaining a Sniffer Egg. New nodes in the Runic Resurgence Guide Advancements Page have been added for the Sculk and Nethersculk Falchions, Deep Dark Core, Ancient Shard, Music Disc Fragments, and several other new items added in this update.","color":"aqua","italic":false},"\n",{"text":"Magic Damage caused by Runic Spells has been given the ability to hit through invincibility cooldowns. This won't make too huge of a difference for older spells aside from Chaos Strike, Flurry, and Storm of Cuts; these spells have been given a new set of functionality and work as they were intended to.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Fixed an issue where the advancement for killing the Necrosculker would not be granted.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Backend changes have been made to improve performance.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"The Necrosculker's loot table has been fleshed out a bit more and drops more items per kill on average.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"The Necrosculker has been altered heavily so that it will now be less punishing to get hit by the boss's attacks. Some attacks will now also be easier to see and avoid, especially those that used to disrupt the player's vision. Its health has been reduced to 1100.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Flurry, Magic Bolt, Enchanted Shield, and Storm of Cuts now have Level 2 variants, which can be casted with higher tier tablets. The upgraded variants have a slew of benefits over the base spells, which can be seen once the appropriate tablets have been achieved.","color":"aqua"}]}}]
tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=10}] ["",{"text":"[Old] Version 0.9 (continued)","underlined":true,"color":"blue","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Nearly every spell across the board has been given a faster cooldown after use. This is so that they become more viable as legitimate means of dealing damage, transportation, and utility in late-game. Some spells have also been given a little boost in their damage dealt.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Added Knowledge Fragments, collectable items which allow you to have a glimpse into the lore of the world.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Removed the previous fix for Withers killing Enderman, as this bug has been fixed in the base game.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Fixed issues with item inconsistencies and modified some lore descriptions.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Buffed Soul Steal to deal Chaos damage instead of plain Magic damage (now cuts through armor, enchantments, and effects). Its base damage has been slightly reduced to prevent it from being too powerful.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Added the Trail Ruins structure to the list of available Search Spell locations.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Added a way to transfer Tablets of Memory with spells on them into their base form by throwing them into water. This is also explained in the Runic Resurgence Guide advancements page.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Fixed an issue with Chaos Strike where most of the bullets sent would travel in incorrect directions.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Entirely reworked the Flurry spell. It no longer uses Fireworks as part of its effect, as these would heavily damage entities around them where this was not intended. The spell now functions correctly, dealing up to 20 damage in total if every burst hits a target.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Darkvision's duration can now be increased by holding a Golden Carrot in your Offhand slot.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Fixed an issue where Magic Bolt could hit the caster.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Ancient Crypt Keepers and Fallen Crypt Keepers now deal slightly more damage.","color":"aqua"}]}}]
scoreboard players add @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=10}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 1

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=9}] ["",{"text":"[Old] Version 0.8","underlined":true,"color":"blue","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"The Ancient Crypt structure now spawns different skeletons, called Fallen Crypt Keepers, which use swords and are more beefy. These skeletons have a rare chance to drop an Ancient Shard, which will have more use later.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"The Ancient Crypt is now an arena of sorts. By throwing a Sculk Catalyst, a Totem of Undying, and 4 Warden Flesh on the Reinforced Deepslate block in the center, you can now summon the Necrosculker Boss, a stationary foe who will try to make you into one of its reanimated corpse pawns.","color":"green","italic":false},"\n",{"text":"Added a new Music Disc for the Boss's theme and for the Ancient Crypt's theme. Craft them with 8 Disc Fragments dropped by the Necrosculker and either 1 Sculk Vein or 1 Warden Flesh. To play them, throw them onto a jukebox They will not work otherwise.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"The Runic Resurgence Guide now has an Entities and Bosses section.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Changed the names and textures of some items.","color":"aqua"}]}}]
scoreboard players add @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=9}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 1

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=8}] ["",{"text":"[Old] Version 0.7","underlined":true,"color":"blue","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Added the Silence Spell [69847] and the Louden Spell [69832].","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Added the Desert Temple, Pillager Outpost, Woodland Mansion, Piglin Bastion, End City, and Ancient Crypt to the available options for the Search Spell.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Reworked most of the Damage Spells that send out bullets. Magic Bolt is now a precise, fast, long-range shot with somewhat low damage. Flurry now only hits 2 entities per blast, making it less oppressive versus groups. Chaos Bolt is now a slow-moving, high-damage, high-AOE bolt. Chaos Strike is now the primary multi-target spell, shooting significantly faster and slightly weaker bullets than Chaos Bolt that pierce through everything the bullets hit.","color":"aqua","italic":false},"\n",{"text":"Fixed an issue where Chaos Bolt coult hurt the caster.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Fixed an issue where Magic Bolt would not count kills as the caster's kills.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Modified a few things in the Runic Resurgence Guide page so information is more clear. Also added the Warden Flesh item to the Items category.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Fixed some typos and incorrect information regarding advancements, spell descriptions and other things.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Added a \"MOTD\" system which will occasionally give some useful information to players. The timer is set to show a message every 10 minutes. This can be disabled per-player by using \"/trigger toggleMOTD\".","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Modified the Runic Tablet's flames to spawn closer together and closer to the player. They can now fit into a 3x3 space and can be clicked on more easily.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Added Cherry Logs and their variants to the available options for the logs-to-chests recipe.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"An additional visual and audio effect has been added to Return Points for when a player is teleporting to them.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Buffed Storm of Cuts. The spell now deals more damage and applies a very weak Levitation and Slow Falling effect to coincide with its wind-based attacks.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Added triggers which allow for increasing and decreasing the total hearts players have. This only goes down to the vanilla default amount and up to the highest hearts reached with Soul Steal's Health Focus. This is changed with \"/trigger decreaseHearts\" and \"/trigger increaseHearts\".","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Every spell can now be input. Spells that are not implemented will simply show a \"spell failed\" message and will immediately enable spell usage again.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Added a new naturally-spawning structure: The Ancient Crypt. This structure is an offshoot of the Ancient City and contains unique loot and music.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Remodeled all of the Tablets to be a little smaller and tilted when held, but larger in item frames and in GUIs. When held, it's more accurate to how they are meant to be in terms of size, but the spells stored on Tablet of Memorys can be seen at a glance more easily in inventories.","color":"green"}]}}]
scoreboard players add @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=8}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 1

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=7}] ["",{"text":"[Old] Version 0.6.1","underlined":true,"color":"blue","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Added the Darkvision Spell [15428].","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Modified the Return Spell to make each Return Point load the chunk it's in. Upon removal of the Return Point, the chunk will no longer be force loaded unless another Return Point exists within the same chunk. Return Points can also no longer be placed within 2 blocks of any other Return Point.","color":"green","italic":false},"\n",{"text":"Overhauled the Runic Resurgence Guide page (the advancement menu thing) to be better sorted and more visually appealing. Each major spell type now has subcategories and is sorted by how the spell functions.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Fixed some typos and incorrect information regarding advancements, spell descriptions and other things.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Added recipes for making dispensers using droppers inside of a bow recipe and for smelting Raw Blocks into their smelted ingot variants (includes the blast furnace as well, takes as much time as smelting individual raw items would). Also added a recipe that allows you to smelt Diorite into Calcite (only in a furnace).","color":"aqua"}]}}]
scoreboard players add @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=7}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 1

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=6}] ["",{"text":"[Old] Version 0.6","underlined":true,"color":"blue","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Added the Chaos Strike Spell [24568] and the Search Spell [78194].","color":"aqua","italic":false},"\n",{"text":"Tweaked the Return Spell to be less loud and to have differing effects when teleporting to the Return Point (to make it more obvious when it is about to work).","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"ACTUALLY fixed the Musical Tablet this time, I promise.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Tweaked Chaotic Sparks to deal -significantly- less damage, and also applies slowness now to make up for the difference.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Tweaked Magic Bolt to fly further, fly faster, and deal more damage to make it viable in comparison to other spells.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Chaos Bolt now does 2 less damage overall since it's unblockable and unmitigatable.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Fixed an issue where Chaos Bolt's Tablet of Memory didn't have a description.","color":"aqua"}]}}]
scoreboard players add @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=6}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 1

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=5}] ["",{"text":"[Old] Version 0.5","underlined":true,"color":"blue","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Added the Magnetize Spell [24568], the Chaos Bolt Spell [13597], and the Return Spell [51294].","color":"aqua","italic":false},"\n",{"text":"Temporarily applied a fix to a bug where Withers could not kill Endermen.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Fixed some issues with the Musical Tablet.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Added some vanilla-esque recipes.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Added a way to convert Runic Tablets to Tablets of Memory and vice versa. Place a Runic Tablet in a Glow Item Frame on a Copper Block, or a Tablet of Memory on a Diamond Block, to convert them.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Added a hidden item, the Casting King's Crown, for testing purposes (removes all spell cooldowns).","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Fixed issues where returning to the overworld from the End would cause players to lose their extra hearts temporarily.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Added Damage Types for various purposes. Some types penetrate armor or resistance or both, some deal increased damage to certain mobs.","color":"green","italic":false}]}}]
scoreboard players add @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=5}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 1

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=4}] ["",{"text":"[Old] Version 0.4","underlined":true,"color":"blue","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Added the Fall Spell [25891].","color":"aqua","italic":false},"\n",{"text":"Modified Soul Steal to hopefully be less laggy.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Added the Musical Tablet (check the Runic Resurgence Guide in the Advancements Menu to see more).","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Added the Warden Flesh item to the Warden Loot Table.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Modified Runic Tablets and Memory Tablets to not activate unless you are holding them when you start sneaking.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Fixed issues with Soul Steal not keeping extra hearts between lives / server restarts.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Added nodes for the Runic Tablet, Musical Tablet, and Tablet of Memory to the Runic Resurgence Guide.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Moved some functions to only run every second instead of every tick for performance.","color":"green","italic":false}]}}]
scoreboard players add @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=4}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 1

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=3}] ["",{"text":"[Old] Version 0.3","underlined":true,"color":"blue","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Overhauled the Runic Tablet: Now you must right-click the flames to input spells. Also modified the time it takes for your Runic Energy to recharge for almost all spells; most spells now have less cooldown, while a couple others have slightly extended cooldown.","color":"aqua","italic":false},"\n",{"text":"Added the Energize Spell [89215] and the Soul Steal Spell [21583].","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Modified Tablet of Memorys to show their stored Spell in their description.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Added the chance to find Zen Shards, Runic Tablets, and Tablet of Memorys to Buried Treasure, Desert Pyramids, Woodland Mansions, and End Cities.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Added new Chained Armor Trim (use a Chain block to apply) and three new Armor Trim Materials (Crying Obsidian, Blaze Powder, and Pink Tulip).","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Added advancements for using specific forms of Soul Steal and for obtaining a Cherry Sapling from Wandering Traders.","color":"green"},"\n",{"text":"Added Ender Stars, a guaranteed drop from Ender Dragons. Also added Netherite Apples, Netherite Stars, and Infinity Stars for use with Soul Steal.","color":"aqua","italic":false}]}}]
scoreboard players add @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=3}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 1

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=2}] ["",{"text":"[Old] Version 0.2.1","underlined":true,"color":"blue","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Modified some Advancements to not have names which are cut off.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Also changed the Absolute Drip advancement so that it now displays progress to all 12 Templates.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"A new set of Advancements shows which Templates have been found. Press \"L\" to see which ones you have! You will need to pick up each Template you've already found again."}]}}]
scoreboard players add @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=2}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 1

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=1}] ["",{"text":"[Old] Version 0.2","underlined":true,"color":"blue","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Added more Advancements for Runic Resurgence as well as one for collecting all Armor Trims in 1.20 Experimental Datapacks.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Also added a ReloadPacks trigger (use /trigger ReloadPacks) for reloading all currently-enabled Datapacks.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Added new Discombobulator statues (Copper Block with Zen Shard on it). Press \"L\" to see its function in Runic Resurgence Guide."}]}}]
scoreboard players add @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=1}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 1

tellraw @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=0}] ["",{"text":"[Old] Version 0.1.1","underlined":true,"color":"blue","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Fixed Loot Tables so that Armor Trims will still spawn in Ancient Cities, Bastion Treasure Rooms, and Jungle Temples.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Also slightly modified the rarity of both types of Tablets. They are now slightly rarer to better match their strength.","color":"aqua"},"\n",{"text":"Added new Advancements for fun, more coming later on."}]}}]
scoreboard players add @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=0}] rr.system.UpdateNumber 1
execute as @s[tag=!RunicUpdateInit] at @s run scoreboard players set @s rr.system.UpdateNumber 0
tag @s[scores={rr.system.UpdateNumber=0},tag=!RunicUpdateInit] add RunicUpdateInit